headline: Goldman Sachs and T. Rowe Price to Launch Alternative Investments for Wealthy Clients by Year-End — What This Shift Means
summary: Goldman Sachs and T. Rowe Price are reportedly collaborating to offer alternative investments to wealthy clients by the end of 2025. But while greater access to specialized assets may deliver higher returns and improve diversification, the trade-offs for investors can include less transparency, higher risks, illiquidity and fees.
